 Juventus forward Cristiano Ronaldo has expressed delight after winning the 2020 Golden Foot award. The former Real Madrid star beat Lionel Messi to the award despite the Argentine winning more Ballons d’Or awards than him. In a post to Instagram, Ronaldo wrote: ‘I am honored to win the Golden Foot award and to be immortalised on the Champion Promenade in Monaco, together with some of the greatest football legends of all time! ‘I am truly humbled and want to thank the fans all over the world for having voted for me’ The Golden Foot award, first introduced in 2003, is an award for players aged 28 or above and can only be won by a recipient once in their career. Previous winners include Roberto Baggio, Alessandro Del Piero and Ronaldinho and Ronaldo looked delighted to join esteemed company.